title Google Cloud Caching Mechanism for V_DIS_TRANSPORTORDER

actor User

participant "TMS Bridge/New Layer" as App
database "TMS" as DB
participant "Expensive SQL (due to procedures)" as View
participant "Datastream (CDC)" as Datastream
queue "Cloud Pub/Sub" as PubSub
participant "Cloud Function (Cache Updater)" as CacheUpdater
database "Cloud Memorystore (Redis)" as Redis

User -> App: Request Query
activate App
App -> Redis: Check Cache
alt Cache Hit
    activate Redis
    Redis -> App: Return Cached Result
    deactivate Redis
else Cache Miss
    App -> DB: Execute Expensive Query
    activate DB
    DB -> View: Compute Expensive View
    activate View
    View -> DB: Return Result
    deactivate View
    DB -> App: Query Result
    deactivate DB
    App -> Redis: Store in Cache (TTL or Permanent)
end
App -> User: Response
deactivate App

== Change Data Capture (CDC) for Cache Invalidation & Update ==

Datastream -> PubSub: Capture Change Event (Insert/Update/Delete)
PubSub -> CacheUpdater: Trigger Cache Invalidation & Update

alt Record Deleted
    CacheUpdater -> Redis: Remove Stale Cache Entry
else Record Updated or Inserted
    CacheUpdater -> DB: Fetch Updated Record
    activate DB
    DB -> CacheUpdater: Return New Data
    deactivate DB
    CacheUpdater -> Redis: Update Cache Entry
end